snippet: A parliamentary session called to commemorate Margaret Thatcher was unusual because of its expected duration and because lawmakers were recalled from recess.
abstract: Debate continues to churn in Britain over legacy of deceased former Prime Min Margaret Thatcher.

byline.original: By JOHN F. BURNS and ALAN COWELL
byline.contributor: John F. Burns reported from London, and Alan Cowell from Paris.

lead_paragraph: A parliamentary session called to commemorate Margaret Thatcher was unusual because of its expected duration and because lawmakers were recalled from recess.

headline.main: Parliament Debates Thatcher Legacy, as Vitriol Flows Online and in Streets
headline.print_headline: Parliament Debates Thatcher Legacy, as Vitriol Flows Online and in Streets
